name: Best Pennsylvania Dutch Chicken Corn Soup
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(3 pound)', 'name': 'whole chickens, cut into pieces'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'quarts', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onions, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped celery'}, {'quantity': '2 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1 ¼', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '10', 'unit': 'ears', 'name': 'fresh corn, kernels cut from cob'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sifted all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'milk'}
steps: Combine chicken, water, onions, celery, salt, nutmeg, and pepper in a large stockpot over medium heat and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, adding water as needed, until chicken is very tender, about 2 hours.. Transfer chicken to a deep dish; pour soup into a large jug or bowl. Cover and refrigerate chicken and soup for 6 to 8 hours.. Remove and discard the layer of fat that has solidified on the surface of soup. Transfer soup into a large pot over medium heat; stir in corn and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until corn is tender, 10 to 15 minutes.. Meanwhile, place 2 of the eggs in a small saucepan and cover with cold water. Bring to a boil and immediately remove from heat. Cover and let eggs stand in hot water for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from hot water, cool, peel, and chop. Set aside.. Chop chilled chicken meat into small chunks; stir into soup.. Beat remaining egg in a medium bowl until light in color. Beat in flour and milk until smooth. Drop pea-sized lumps of rivel dough into the soup, a few at a time, to make small dumplings. Cook, stirring constantly, until dumplings hold their shape and float to the surface, 2 to 5 minutes. Stir in chopped egg.

Chill pie in refrigerator until filling is set, at least 1 hour.

steps: Prepare waterbath canner, jars and lids according to manufacturers instructions, if preserving. Prepare and measure ingredients for recipe.. ingredients: {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'whole wheat flour'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cornmeal'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'granular no-calorie sucralose sweetener (e.g., Splenda ®)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg whites'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'plain nonfat yogurt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'skim milk'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cooking spray'}
steps: Whisk both flours, oats, cornmeal, sweetener, baking powder, salt, baking soda, and cinnamon together in a medium bowl.. Whisk egg whites, yogurt, milk, and water together in a separate bowl. name: Chicken Corn Chowder
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'chicken carcass'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'bay leaf'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, diced'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'shallots, diced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cubes', 'name': 'chicken bouillon, crumbled'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'dried parsley'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'potatoes, peeled and diced'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'frozen corn kernels'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'heavy cream'}
steps: Place chicken carcass (and any leftover skin and meat and other bones) in a large pot and cover with cold water. Add bay leaf, and bring to a boil. Reduce heat, and simmer 60 to 90 minutes. Remove from heat, cool slightly, and strain. Remove chicken meat from carcass, and chop into bite-size pieces.. In a large saucepan over medium heat, melt butter. Cook onion and shallots in butter until translucent. Pour in strained broth and chicken meat and stir in bouillon, parsley, salt, pepper, potatoes and corn. Simmer 15 minutes, until potatoes are cooked and corn is tender. Remove from heat and stir in cream.

name: Sugar-Free Peach and Banana Cobbler
ingredients: {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '', 'name': 'white peaches, pitted and sliced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'bananas, sliced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'sugar substitute, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'skim milk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'corn oil'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease an 8-inch square baking dish.. Mix peaches, bananas, 2 tablespoons flour, and 1 teaspoon sugar substitute in a bowl until fruit is coated; spread into the bottom of the prepared baking dish.. Whisk 1 cup flour, baking powder, salt, and cinnamon in the same bowl used to mix fruit. Stir in skim milk, egg, corn oil, remaining 2 teaspoons sugar substitute, and vanilla until well combined. Pour batter in an even layer over fruit.. Bake in the preheated oven until cobbler is golden brown and a toothpick inserted into the middle comes out clean, about 30 minutes. Remove to a wire rack and cool in the pan for at least 20 minutes before serving.
